abstract: To transform his Williamsburg townhouse into a whimsical playground, an architect consulted his own early memories (treehouses were involved).
snippet: To transform his Williamsburg townhouse into a whimsical playground, an architect consulted his own early memories (treehouses were involved).
lead_paragraph: Sometimes, when life changes, your home needs to change too. Or at least that’s what Jun Aizaki, the founder of the architecture and design firm Crème, determined after he started a family.

main: A Brooklyn Home Designed With Fun in Mind

abstract: Lawmakers’ objections to an obscure Chinese semiconductor company and tough Covid-19 restrictions are hurting Apple’s ability to make new iPhones in China.
snippet: Lawmakers’ objections to an obscure Chinese semiconductor company and tough Covid-19 restrictions are hurting Apple’s ability to make new iPhones in China.
lead_paragraph: Every September, Apple unveils its latest phones at its futuristic Silicon Valley campus. A few weeks later, tens of millions of its newest handsets, assembled by legions of seasonal workers hired by its suppliers, are shipped from Chinese factories to customers around the world.

main: Apple Built Its Empire With China. Now Its Foundation Is Showing Cracks.
print_headline: China Turning Into a Liability For the iPhone

abstract: The appointment of Lt. Gen. Syed Asim Munir comes after weeks of intense speculation and backstage negotiations over who would lead the nuclear-armed military.
snippet: The appointment of Lt. Gen. Syed Asim Munir comes after weeks of intense speculation and backstage negotiations over who would lead the nuclear-armed military.
lead_paragraph: ISLAMABAD, Pakistan — Pakistan on Thursday announced the rise of a new army chief, a changing of the guard that many consider as crucial to Pakistani affairs as civilian political cycles and that comes at a moment of fierce debate over the military’s power in politics.

main: Pakistan Names a New Army Chief, Amid Political Drama Centered on the Military
print_headline: Commander Comes In At a Challenging Time

abstract: The photo-editing program can now generate images of almost anything. Its maker has a plan it hopes will make this less risky than it sounds.
snippet: The photo-editing program can now generate images of almost anything. Its maker has a plan it hopes will make this less risky than it sounds.
lead_paragraph: Photoshop is the granddaddy of image-editing apps, the O.G. of our airbrushed, Facetuned media ecosystem and a product so enmeshed in the culture that it’s a verb, an adjective and a frequent lament of rappers. Photoshop is also widely used. More than 30 years since the first version was released, professional photographers, graphic designers and other visual artists the world over reach for the app to edit much of the imagery you see online, in print and on billboards, bus stops, posters, product packaging and anything else the light touches.

main: A.I. Photoshopping Is About to Get Very Easy. Maybe Too Easy.

abstract: Tehran has quietly stepped up the sale of drone technology to countries outside the Middle East as it seeks to become a player in the international market.
snippet: Tehran has quietly stepped up the sale of drone technology to countries outside the Middle East as it seeks to become a player in the international market.
lead_paragraph: Iran has made steady advances in the design and production of military drones in recent years, and has stepped up their transfer to militant groups across the Middle East as it seeks to shift the dynamics of battlefields from Yemen to Gaza.

main: Iran Ramps Up Drone Exports, Signaling Global Ambitions
print_headline: Iran Steps Up Drone Exports as It Seeks to Build Global Clout

abstract: Federal prosecutors in Brooklyn said in a complaint unsealed Tuesday that Ibrahim Alhussayen, 42, had sent threats on Instagram to Saudi citizens living in the United States and Canada.
snippet: Federal prosecutors in Brooklyn said in a complaint unsealed Tuesday that Ibrahim Alhussayen, 42, had sent threats on Instagram to Saudi citizens living in the United States and Canada.
lead_paragraph: A Saudi citizen who prosecutors say used an anonymous Instagram account to harass and threaten dissidents, most of them women, has been charged with lying to federal officials, according a complaint unsealed Tuesday in federal court in Brooklyn.

main: Saudi Man Bullied Dissidents via Instagram and Lied to F.B.I., U.S. Says
print_headline: In Complaint, Officials Say Saudi Troll Lied to F.B.I.

abstract: An Austrian immigrant, he was one of the so-called Ritchie Boys, who were trained at a secret Army intelligence camp to serve in World War II.
snippet: An Austrian immigrant, he was one of the so-called Ritchie Boys, who were trained at a secret Army intelligence camp to serve in World War II.
lead_paragraph: Maximilian Lerner, an Austrian-born Jew who was among the last surviving members of a World War II unit, many of them European Jews, who were recruited to learn espionage and intelligence skills and then employ them in Europe and the Pacific to help United States forces as they swept toward victory, died on Sept. 10 at his home in Manhattan. He was 98.

main: Maximilian Lerner, Whose Espionage Skills Helped Win a War, Dies at 98
print_headline: Maximilian Lerner, 98, World War II Spy

lead_paragraph: KYIV, Ukraine — Russia’s domestic intelligence service announced the arrest of eight people on Wednesday in connection with the weekend bombing of the bridge linking Russia to the occupied Crimean Peninsula. Five are citizens of Russia, according to the agency, the F.S.B., and the others are Ukrainian and Armenian.

abstract: It’s fine to have money and power, as long as you don’t admit how much you want them.
snippet: It’s fine to have money and power, as long as you don’t admit how much you want them.
lead_paragraph: My friends who have never seen “Succession,” the hit HBO show that will soon come to an end, say that they have no interest in watching rich people behaving badly. The darkly comic series certainly fits that bill: It follows the travails of the Roy family, the patriarch of which, Logan Roy, is an avatar of Rupert Murdoch, and whose children, Shiv, Kendall and Roman, jockey endlessly, and haplessly, to inherit his throne.

main: How ‘Succession’ Busts One of America’s Most Cherished Myths

abstract: Four people died when a storm sank a boat in northern Italy. Then it emerged that 21 of those aboard had worked for Israeli or Italian intelligence, igniting a speculative frenzy.
snippet: Four people died when a storm sank a boat in northern Italy. Then it emerged that 21 of those aboard had worked for Israeli or Italian intelligence, igniting a speculative frenzy.
lead_paragraph: The black clouds appeared quickly, sneaking up on sun-seeking revelers on the lake in northern Italy, interrupting early-evening aperitivi and lakefront strolls. A weather warning issued earlier in the day had not foreseen the violence of the storm that burst over the lake, with winds so extreme they sank a boat, killing four of its 23 passengers.

main: Tragedy Strikes a Boat Full of Spies, and Conspiracy Theories Mount
print_headline: A Boat Full of Spies, a Deadly Storm and a Flurry of Theories

original: By Elisabetta Povoledo and Ronen Bergman
